import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='precipitation', bins=20, kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1)
    plt.legend(['Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['precipitation'].median())])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Precipitation')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m')

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='month', y='temp', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('How does the temperature vary throughout the year in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.legend(['Temperature'], loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind speed and temperature in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Wind Speed')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.legend(title='Temperature', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month_name()
    data['sunny'] = data['weather'] == 'Sunny'

    sunny_days = data.groupby('month')['sunny'].sum().reset_index()

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='month', y='sunny', data=sunny_days, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the frequency of sunny days in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Sunny Days')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Sunny Days', loc='upper right', labels=['Sunny'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.dates as mdates

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['daylight_hours'] = data['daylight'] / 60

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='daylight_hours', data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('How does the amount of daylight vary throughout the year in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Daylight Hours')

    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(mdates.MonthLocator())
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%b'))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    max_daylight = data['daylight_hours'].max()
    ax.axhline(max_daylight, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Daylight: {max_daylight:.2f} hours')
    ax.legend()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
